# Adding Images to Service Page

The user wants to display photos inside the service item boxes on the "Community Service" (지역 섬김) page. Currently, these boxes only display icons.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> I will replace the existing icons with images. If you want to keep both or use a specific layout (e.g., image on top, image on left), please let me know. For now, I will implement a **vertical card layout** with the image at the top of each box, as this is a standard and attractive way to display rich content.

## Proposed Changes

### Data Layer
#### [MODIFY] [churchData.js](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/산돌교회 홈페이지/src/data/churchData.js)
- Add an `image` property to each item in `service.items`.
- Use Unsplash placeholder images matching the context (food, children, cafe, beauty/haircut).

### Component Layer
#### [MODIFY] [ServicePage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/산돌교회 홈페이지/src/pages/ServicePage.jsx)
- Update the item rendering loop.
- Remove the `iconMap` and icon rendering logic (or make it a fallback).
- Change the card layout to display the `item.image` prominently (e.g., `w-full h-48 object-cover` at the top of the card).
- Adjust styling for the text content to sit below the image.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- None.

### Manual Verification
- Run the development server (`npm run dev`).
- Navigate to `http://localhost:5173/service`.
- Verify that each of the four service boxes now displays an image instead of an icon.
- Check responsiveness on mobile and desktop.
